<TITLE> 1 killed, 100 injured in Hobiganj village brawl </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Hobiganj, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  One person was killed and up to 100 injured in a clash between two rival groups at a village in Lakhai upazila, Hobiganj, on Wednesday, police said. Kuddus Miah, 35, was killed in the clash, which occurred over establishing supremacy between two rival groups in Bamai village, officer in charge of Lakhai Police Station MA Gani told bdnews24.com. Of the injured, the conditions of at least 10 villagers were critical. They were sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Others were admitted to Hobiganj Adhunik Sadar Hospital and Lakhai Upazila Health Complex, Gani said. Two rival groups of Bamai  one led by former Union Parishad chairman Nurul Islam Dudu Miah and another by a local leader Piari Miah - clashed from 9am to 12pm, he said. At least five houses were set on fire during the clash. Incidents of looting were also reported. Locals alleged that police were inactive during the clash and some houses were set ablaze and looted in presence of them. Police, however, denied the allegations. Local police chief Gani said they reached the scene by 10am and tried to bring the situation under control. The two rival groups have a long-standing enmity, locals said. bdnews24.
